# apps (and how it have to work)

- **Description:** This section focuses on building the application modules that will run within the OS simulation, including their structure, registration, and integration with the system core.

## 1. apps list and their structure

- **Description:** Define a list of applications to be included in the OS simulation, along with their folder structure and basic functionality.

### terminal

- **Description:** A command-line interface application that allows users to execute commands and interact with the system.
- **Folder Structure:**
  - /src/apps/terminal
    - index.tsx (main component)
    - model.ts (state management and logic)
    - styles.css (styling for the terminal)
- **Functionality:**
  - Basic command execution (e.g., `ls`, `cd`, `echo`)
  - Displaying command output
  - Handling user input
- **Integration:** The terminal app will be registered in the App Registry and will interact with the Process Manager to create a new process when launched.
- **style** the terminal app to have a classic look with a dark background and green text, mimicking traditional command-line interfaces. 


